A: You are using the wrong method for querying. You should use the query method of SQLiteDatabase, not the query method of your adapter class.
Here is how you should do it:

```java
public class LoginActivity extends Activity {
    EditText nameText, phoneText;
    Button registeredButton, newUser;
    AdapterClass ad1;

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.login);

        newUser = (Button) findViewById(R.id.new_user);
        newUser.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
            @Override
            public void onClick(View v) {
                nameText = (EditText) findViewById(R.id.user_text);
                phoneText = (EditText) findViewById(R.id.pass_text);
                String name = nameText.getText().toString();
                String phone = phoneText.getText().toString();

                ad1 = new AdapterClass(getApplicationContext(), DatabaseDetail.REGISTER);
                ad1.Open();

                Cursor cursor = ad1.query("SELECT * FROM CUS_REGISTER WHERE CUS_NAME=? AND CUS_PHONE=? AND col2 IS NOT NULL", new String[]{name, phone});
                startManagingCursor(cursor);
                cursor.moveToFirst();
                if (cursor.getCount() > 0) {
                    Toast.makeText(getApplicationContext(), "Sucess", 5000).show();
                } else {
                    // handle the case where no records are found
                }
            }
        });
    }
}
```

In your AdapterClass, you should have a method like this:

```java
public Cursor query(String table, String[] columns, String selection, String[] selectionArgs, String groupBy, String having, String orderBy) {
    return database.query(table, columns, selection, selectionArgs, groupBy, having, orderBy);
}
```

This method allows you to specify the table, columns, selection, selection arguments, group by, having, and order by for the query.

Please replace `"SELECT * FROM CUS_REGISTER WHERE CUS_NAME=? AND CUS_PHONE=? AND col2 IS NOT NULL"` with your actual query.

Also, make sure that the column `col2` is not null in your database. If it can be null, you should remove the `IS NOT NULL` part from your query.

I hope this helps. Let me know if you have any further questions.

Note: You should not call `db.close()` in your adapter class. It should be called in your activity class when you are done with the database operations.

